solution: ```class Solution {
    public int trailingZeroes(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n > 0) {
            n /= 5;
            count += n;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Counts factors of 5 in n! by repeatedly dividing n by 5 and summing the quotients; each division represents the contribution of the next power of 5.

